snippet.textDisplay:
Chris, my man! I missed your premiere, and feel rightly bad about that, so don't judge me. I've been sitting here on this couch for 6 straight weeks now! Practically sitting on the floor now it's gotten so loose. I should just switch it around with one of the other cushions, but I've grown fat and lazy. Lazy anyway. But, once again, your infectious tempo inside outmatched and outweighed the infection blues outside and got me up and moving and waving my arms and lip-syncing and kicking up my feet and even pouring myself a wicked glass of chocolate milk! Yeah, baby! Livin' life again on the edge!


But, 3:27 later, I was back on that cushion, sinking to the floor, trying to remember what just happened. You gotta do another one. Just for my sake. And that'a all that matters. It's all about me.


All that above nonsense said...Thank you, again, for being who you are, what you do, and for sharing a heart (and talent) that's as big as the outdoors we all knew. And that we will know again. Love you.
